# GitHub Fine-Grained Personal Access Token for CodeBuild/CodePipeline
#
# How to create:
# 1. Go to: https://github.com/settings/tokens?type=beta
# 2. Click "Generate new token" (Fine-grained tokens)
# 3. Fill in:
#    - Token name: lab-scaling-peak-load
#    - Expiration: 30 days (default)
#    - Description: Token for CI/CD pipeline (optional)
#
# 4. Resource owner:
#    - Select your GitHub organization or personal account
#
# 5. Repository access:
#    - Select "Only select repositories"
#    - Choose: lab-scaling-peak-load repository
#
# 6. Permissions (Repository permissions):
#    - Administration: Read-only (for webhook setup)
#    - Contents: Read and write (for source code access)
#    - Webhooks: Read and write (for CodePipeline triggers)
#    - Commit statuses: Read and write (for build status)
#
# 7. Click "Generate token"
# 8. Copy the token and paste it below (PAT_11... format)
#
# WARNING: This token has repository access permissions.
# - Never commit this file to version control
# - Rotate the token periodically
# - Revoke immediately if compromised
#
GITHUB_TOKEN_LAB_SCALING=your_fine_grained_token_here
